cs.DC, cs.PF, cs.DS, cs.SC, cs.SE 

Reasoning: 

- cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing): The paper focuses on analyzing parallel I/O use on a national supercomputing service, which is a distributed and parallel computing system. 
- cs.PF (Performance): The paper discusses the use of performance data to identify potential issues and improve I/O use, and also presents results from analysis of I/O performance. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper describes the use of tools to collect and analyze data on I/O usage patterns, which involves algorithms and data structures. 
- cs.SC (Scientific Computing): The paper discusses the use of a national supercomputing service for scientific research, and analyzes I/O usage patterns associated with different research areas. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper describes the use of software tools (LASSi and SAFE) to collect and analyze I/O performance data, and also discusses future directions for this work.
